Some tips for new players When I'm reading people, I always look for these two things - Interactions with other players. Mafia already knows all roles, and thus their interactions are biased, whereas the interactions of townies with others aren't biased -> they don't know alignments for sure, and only have actual thoughts on the matter. - Whether someone is pushing an agenda. Mafia often plans ahead to work towards a win, so when someone does that, it's super sus. Think of someone saying 'X and Y def has to include a mafia, but I don't think both are.' Chances are that X and Y are both town, and whoever said that wants to lynch them in back to back days
